1. Install Required Tools
Python (3.8–3.11 recommended)
Download from Python.org

Visual Studio Installer → Desktop Development with C++
Needed because dlib (used by face_recognition) compiles C++ extensions.

CMake (>= 3.22)
Download from CMake.org

Git (optional but useful for cloning repos).


2. Create & Activate Virtual Environment
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate


3. Install Python Dependencies
Inside your Project Agumentation/ folder, run:
pip install opencv-python
pip install numpy
pip install pandas
pip install cmake
pip install dlib
pip install face-recognition
pip install pillow
pip install tk



4. Project Assets
Student Images go into Students/.
Logo goes into logo/logo.png.
Attendance.csv will be updated automatically.
Encodefile.p stores encoded face data.



5. Run the System

Encode student faces first:
python encode_students.py
→ This generates Encodefile.p.


Launch face recognition GUI:
python face_recognition_gui.py

Attendance will be marked in Attendance.csv.



